    "### Time series decomposition\n",
    "\n",
    "Let $(X_t)_{t=1}^T$ be a time series. A classical additive decomposition writes\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "X_t = T_t + S_t + R_t,\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where:\n",
    "\n",
    "- $T_t$ is the **trend** component,\n",
    "- $S_t$ is the **seasonal** component,\n",
    "- $R_t$ is the **remainder** (or residual) component.\n",
    "\n",
    "In this lab you will implement a simple decomposition from scratch.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Moving averages\n",
    "\n",
    "A moving average is often used to estimate the trend. For an odd window size $q = 2h+1$, the centered moving average is\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\operatorname{MA}_q(x)_t = \frac{1}{q} \\sum_{j=-h}^{h} x_{t+j},\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "for all indices $t$ such that the full window is available.\n",
    "\n",
    "Near the boundaries, you may return `np.nan`.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
