   "source": [
    "#### Seasonal component\n",
    "\n",
    "Assume that the period $p$ is known. Once an estimate $m_t$ of the trend has been computed, define the detrended series\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "d_t = x_t - m_t.\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "A simple estimate of the seasonal pattern is obtained by averaging the detrended observations with the same position inside the period. For $k \\in \\{0, 1, \\ldots, p-1\\}$,\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\tilde{s}_k = \f",
    "rac{1}{N_k} \\sum_{t : (t-1) \bmod p = k} d_t,\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where the sum is taken only over indices for which $d_t$ is available.\n",
    "\n",
    "To make the additive decomposition identifiable, it is common to center the seasonal pattern so that\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\sum_{k=0}^{p-1} s_k = 0.\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Then we repeat this pattern over time to obtain $s_t$.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
